 From the DrScheme FAQ:
 
 	The real problem may be that the installer is unable to write
 the 	DrScheme files to your hard drive, or the installer may be
 unable 	to modify the Start menu. In this case, check to make sure there
 is disk space available, and contact your system maintainer to 	make
 sure that you have the appropriate access privileges.
 
 	More details about this problem are available from the Wise
 Solutions KnowledgeBase at
 
 	   http://www.wise.com/displayArticle.asp?articleno=1034
 
 -- Paul
 
 
